Description:
    Installs the Oroshi engine into your Rails application.

    This generator will:
    - Create Oroshi initializer (config/initializers/oroshi.rb)
    - Create User model (if not exists)
    - Configure Devise routes
    - Mount the Oroshi engine in routes
    - Copy migrations from engine
    - Copy Solid Queue/Cache/Cable schemas
    - Provide post-install instructions

Example:
    rails generate oroshi:install

    This will create:
        config/initializers/oroshi.rb
        app/models/user.rb (if not exists)
        db/queue_schema.rb
        db/cache_schema.rb
        db/cable_schema.rb

    And update:
        config/routes.rb (mount engine + devise routes)

Options:
    --skip-migrations    Skip copying migrations
    --skip-devise        Skip Devise setup
    --skip-user-model    Skip User model generation

After running this generator:
    1. Configure database.yml for multi-database setup
    2. Run: bin/rails db:create db:migrate
    3. Load Solid schemas:
       bin/rails db:schema:load:queue
       bin/rails db:schema:load:cache
       bin/rails db:schema:load:cable
    4. Seed demo data (optional): bin/rails db:seed
    5. Start server: bin/rails server
